      </div>
      <div class="text">
    John Mosley, who calls himself and his trademarked line of apparel and accessories the &quot;Popular Nobody,&quot; is one of the most sought after artist in the beauty industry.
    <br><br/>
    With over 16 years of passion and experience, John and his career have been on a steady incline, seeing his dreams unfold since he started in Long Beach, California. John is the founder/CEO and team lead for his Popular Nobody team and brand.
    <br><br/>
    His hard work, insatiable drive, and unstoppable tenacity for his craft allow John to keep his chair in a constant rotation of devoted clientele at his shop Popular Grooming Lounge in Dallas Texas. In 2017 John was named Modern Salons Top 100 industry game changers, 2019 he was named Educator of the Year, doing over 250 class and just about all major hair shows in 2018.
    <br><br/>
    John's individualized aesthetic has been showcased onstage in Eminem and Rihanna's acclaimed &quot;Monster Tour" and a film titled Deuces that will be featured on Netflix. John's large list of clients includes actors Larenz Tate and Idrs Elba, along with some of the most talked-about names in the music industry today, such as Kendrick Lamar and the TDE family, Jidenna, and many more. No stranger to the athletic world, John also works with the NFL Players Association (NFLPA), Major League Baseball players/teams and a few NBA players.
    <br><br/>
    In addition to movies, television, and commercials, John's visually precise looks have been published in GQ, New York Times Style, British GQ, Vogue, the cover of Billboard, Black Enterprise, Ebony, and Rolling Stone.
    <br><br/>
    Participating in Paul Mitchell Schools' Men's Cutting DVD as well he also help write and create the Paul Mitchell Barber Curriculum. Now John spends his time building his team and their brand. Education is the key and their goals are too share their knowledge, passion, laughs, life's ups and downs, and love. John is an inspiration and lifelong mentor to many because a statement he stands by.
    <br><br/>
    &quot;Always remain a Popular Nobody while staying Humble and Hungry&quot;
      </div>
